snippet.textDisplay:
Fuuuuu. OMFG YESSS! THIS WAS AMAZING! They are living the dream right here. Reptiles are so freakin' awesome. AND they got to hold a scorpion AND tarantula!?

I love how Ethan freakin' lied right before having to hold a tarantula. They are pretty cool and weird to hold for the first time. Same with scorpions. Weird little feetsies. It's awesome.

Love the various lizards.

The only thing I would've noped on out of was the alligator one. ESPECIALLY after being told one of them had bit him TWICE?! Heck no.

But the snakes? I mean, I wouldn't be able to stand and hold them: too heavy. But that's so awesome.

Jay was (mostly) hilarious. That energy is perfect for Unus Annus.

I just hope all the animals are well taken care of at Prehistoric Pets... Obviously it's hard to tell from a video, and I've never seen a place (outside of a zoo) with alligators that are fed that way, for example. And I've heard of places keeping reptiles in places too small for them. Hopefully that's not the case here.

All in all - loved that they got to experience these awesome animals. So much fun.
